main event: A radar station in Barbers Point, Hawaii detected an unidentified object in the sky on October 19, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed on radar for 23 minutes, traveling at a high rate of speed and at extreme altitude.
The object made a turn to the left and then back to the right before disappearing from radar contact.
The radar operators described the object as looking like a missile, and made radio calls to try to make contact with it.
The cause of the radar interference was not determined, and the object was classified as 'unidentified' in the report.
The report mentions that the sighting was made by 'MAX, BAR, PT', likely referring to the radar operators on duty.
